# Automated File Organizer

Automated File Organizer is a professional Python command-line application that sorts files in a selected directory into categorized folders such as Images, Documents, Videos, Audio, Archives, Executables, Code Files, Spreadsheets, Presentations, PDFs, and Others.

The project is designed to be clean, modular, reliable, and suitable for internship submission or open-source review.

## Intern Details


| Intern ID | CITS4930 |
| Full Name | J.Angelin Jeba |
| No. of Weeks | [4] |
| Project Name | Automated File Organizer |

## Project Scope

The application organizes files by extension, supports recursive traversal, offers dry-run previews, handles duplicate filenames safely, and prints a readable summary after each run.

## Objectives

- Reduce manual file sorting effort.
- Organize files into predictable folders.
- Provide a safe, non-destructive experience.
- Deliver a polished and well-documented codebase.

## Features

- Category-based file organization.
- Recursive organization across nested folders.
- Dry-run mode for previewing actions.
- Duplicate filename handling with automatic suffixing.
- Clear summary reporting at the end of each run.
- Optional JSON configuration for custom categories and ignored directories.
- Graceful handling of invalid paths, permission errors, and unexpected file-operation failures.
- Structured logging and readable console output.

## Technology Stack

- Python 3.10+
- Standard Library only
- unittest for automated tests
- argparse for the command-line interface

